Message.MsgText: ADMS0209W=ADMS0209W: The configuration synchronization complete for cell, errors occurred.
Message.Explanation: This is the final event that will appear, the synchronization for all active nodes is complete. Some errors did occur.
Message.UserResponse: Check the logs and previous events

Message.MsgText: ADMS0213E=ADMS0213E: The deployment manager did not reapply automatic synchronization on the {0} node.
Message.Explanation: An error occurred when the deployment manager tried to reapply automatic synchronization on the node.
Message.UserResponse: Using wsadmin tooling, call the setAttribute action and set the autoSyncEnabled attribute to true on the NodeSync MBean for this node.

Message.MsgText: ADMS0110E=ADMS0110E: An exception occurred getting the security credentials. {0}

Message.MsgText: ADMS0023I=ADMS0023I: A synchronization operation reached the iteration limit.
Message.Explanation: If the cell repository is updated during a synchronization, the operation iterates to pick up the new updates. In this case, the repository has been updated multiple times and the synchronization operation has iterated the maximum number of times, possibly without picking up all of the updates.
Message.UserResponse: If automatic synchronization mode is in effect, do nothing. The next synchronization will pick up any remaining updates that might have been missed. If automatic synchronization is disabled, invoke another synchronization.

Message.MsgText: ADMS0003I=ADMS0003I: The configuration synchronization completed successfully.
Message.Explanation: Any new and modified configuration files are successfully moved from the deployment manager to the node.
Message.UserResponse: No user action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMS0212I=ADMS0212I: Disabling automatic synchronization mode after 5 consecutive failures to synchronize
Message.Explanation: Automatic synchronization is disabled due to continued synchronization failures
Message.UserResponse: Check for system anomalis that caused the synchronization failures and correct the condition

Message.MsgText: ADMS0019I=ADMS0019I: Automatic synchronization mode is disabled.
Message.Explanation: This informational message indicates a change in the synchronization mode.
Message.UserResponse: No user action is required.

Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to set the automatic synchronization interval to a negative value. The value must be a positive number of minutes.
Message.UserResponse: Retry the operation with a valid interval value.

Message.Explanation: The system cannot send the synchronization request to the indicated node. This problem most likely occurred because the node agent is not running.
Message.UserResponse: Start the node agent.

Message.MsgText: ADMS0021I=ADMS0021I: The system detects {0} cell repository objects.
Message.Explanation: None

Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMS0017I=ADMS0017I: An unexpected error occurred while trying to initiate automatic synchronization.
Message.Explanation: Automatic synchronization is not starting successfully. You can use manual synchronization to move configuration files to the node.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: ADMS0210E=ADMS0210E: Unable to check Node Synchronization state for node: {0} declaring failed.
Message.Explanation: An error occurred when checking the synchronization state, the synchronization to that node has been declared failed.
Message.UserResponse: Check the logs and previous events

Message.MsgText: ADMS0206I=ADMS0206I: The configuration synchronization failed for node: {0}.
Message.Explanation: Configuration synchronization failed for the stated node.
Message.UserResponse: Check the logs in deployment manager and nodeagent

Message.MsgText: ADMS0020E=ADMS0020E: A synchronization operation received an exception from the repository while updating document {0}. {1}
Message.Explanation: The synchronization operation can continue, but the repository update for the indicated document is not made.
Message.UserResponse: The situation might correct itself on the next synchronization. If not, examine the repository exception and take appropriate action.

Message.MsgText: ADMS0036E=ADMS0036E: The configuration synchronization failed.
Message.Explanation: Configuration files cannot be synchronized between the deployment manager and the node.
Message.UserResponse: Look at the other log entries to get information on the specific error. The deployment manager might be unreachable.

Message.MsgText: ADMS0205I=ADMS0205I: The configuration synchronization completed successfully for node: {0}.
Message.Explanation: Configuration synchronization is complete for the stated node.
Message.UserResponse: None

Message.MsgText: ADMS0015E=ADMS0015E: The synchronization request cannot be completed because the node agent cannot communicate with the deployment manager.
Message.Explanation: The node agent cannot establish a connection to the deployment manager. The deployment manager process is probably not running.
Message.UserResponse: Check the state of the deployment manager process. Restart the deployment manager.

Message.MsgText: ADMS0204E=ADMS0204E: The system is unable to generate synchronization request for node: {0}. Another node synchronization operation might be in progress on the same node.
Message.Explanation: The deployment manager was unable to generate a request to the nodeagent residing on the stated node.
Message.UserResponse: Check the logs in deployment manager and nodeagent

Message.MsgText: ADMS0012E=ADMS0012E: The system is unable to create an administrative client connection: {0}.
Message.Explanation: The node agent cannot connect to the deployment manager during a synchronization. This error can result from the deployment manager being stopped, or can result from a network error.

Message.MsgText: ADMS0028E=ADMS0028E: An unexpected exception {0} occurred in building the cache for J2CResourceAdapter synchronization from the resources.xml file. The application synchronization logic does not work for deletions or modifications of binaries in this case.

Message.UserResponse: Delete the uninstalled resource adapter archive (RAR) file manually.
